---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Cost & receipts · Squeezy"
  description="Squeezy tool-call saving, read slicing, receipts, spill handles, lazy schemas, and budget counters."
  activeDoc="/docs/cost-receipts/"
  eyebrow="cost & receipts"
  heading="The cost work happens before the provider request."
  lead="Squeezy is built on the assumption that model context is expensive and local analysis is comparatively cheap. The agent does deterministic local work before paid model tokens."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Read optimization</h2>
    <div class="doc-card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">read_slice</span>
        <h3>Exact ranges</h3>
        <p>After graph navigation narrows a symbol or code region, Squeezy can send only that slice instead of a whole file.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">diff reads</span>
        <h3>Changed code only</h3>
        <p>read_slice can target worktree, staged, branch-base, index, or last-receipt baselines so review turns focus on changed ranges.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">receipts</span>
        <h3>Do not resend unchanged bytes</h3>
        <p>Repeated read-style outputs can return compact receipt stubs when Squeezy has already shown the model the same content.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">spills</span>
        <h3>Preview now, exact output later</h3>
        <p>Large tool outputs are stored locally behind handles. The model receives a shaped preview and can request exact ranges only when needed.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Tool-call budget</h2>
    <p>Squeezy tracks and surfaces tool calls, read bytes, search-file counts, receipt hits, output spills, denials, provider tokens, cache counters, and estimated cost. Budget pressure becomes visible in the session instead of being hidden in provider invoices.</p>
    <pre><code>SQUEEZY_MAX_TOOL_CALLS_PER_TURN
SQUEEZY_MAX_TOOL_BYTES_READ_PER_TURN
SQUEEZY_MAX_SEARCH_FILES_PER_TURN
SQUEEZY_MAX_TOOL_RESULT_BYTES_PER_ROUND
SQUEEZY_TOOL_SPILL_THRESHOLD_BYTES
SQUEEZY_EXPLORATION_COMPILER=off</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Schema loading</h2>
    <p>Core tools stay visible. Long-tail and MCP tools can be advertised through a compact index and loaded lazily with `load_tool_schema`, preserving smaller initial prompts while keeping tools discoverable.</p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
